news.title: Chintels India to conduct structural audit of Chintels Paradiso
news.para: Police have booked the builder and the construction contractor for negligence while the district administration has ordered an inquiry into the matter, according to officials.

news.title: Sale of residential and commercial sites on freehold basis in Chandigarh
news.para: With this move, sale of hundreds of commercial and residential properties of all the departments of the Chandigarh administration, namely Chandigarh Housing Board, municipal corporation and estate office, will be started through e-auction.

news.title: SDMC Budget: Proposal to hike property tax rejected
news.para: The SDMC on Thursday also announced that tax on one property will be exempted for native residents living in rural areas of south Delhi.

news.title: Chintels Paradiso: Death toll rises to two; builder booked
news.para: Police have booked the builder of Chintels Paradiso, a residential complex, and the construction contractor for negligence, while the district administration has ordered an inquiry into the matter, they said.

news.title: Kochi civic body plans 15% cess on property tax
news.para: The corporation is head-deep in a financial crisis which has evolved over the past several years. The local body owes the contractors a huge amount and lack of funds has impacted the implementation of many projects.

news.title: Property cards to replace 7/12 extract in Nashik
news.para: The 7/12 extract is from the Record of Rights that primarily has mention of the quality of land – cultivable or not, and also about the crops in the field.

news.title: Provide housing facility to urban poor: Bihar CM
news.para: Nitish, who reviewed the work being done by the UDHD, said the scheme for the provision of housing facilities to the homeless urban poor was part of the Bihar Atmanirbhar vision that underlined the Saat Nischchay-II programme of the government.

news.title: Builders urge Rajasthan government for tax incentives to boost industry
news.para: After first lockdown, both consumers and real estate industry faced a setback as stamp duty was increased to 6% from 5%. Also, with 1% registration fee and 30% other taxes, the total stamp duty had gone up to 8.8%.

news.title: Market value of land in new Andhra Pradesh districts to see upward revision
news.para: Sensing that the number of land registrations have already picked up pace in the new district headquarters, the government has decided to mop up additional revenue by increasing the market value of land.

news.title: Land diverted via 22,000 illegal registries in Gurugram division in four years: Probe
news.para: Of these, more than 15,000 were in Gurgaon district alone. Through the illegal registries, land notified as a controlled area – which has certain safeguards – was diverted for construction, officials said.

news.title: Nuvoco Vistas Corp to invest Rs 1,950 crore as part of expansion plans
news.para: Besides, Nuvoco Vistas will invest Rs 400 crore on debottlenecking and upgradation of projects at its existing plants and Rs 50 crore to set up alternate fuel material handling facilities.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Rs 1 crore cash found in income tax searches on developers
news.para: “About 50 officers and 100 staff members participated in the searches. They were brought from the major cities of Gujarat. Three brokers associated with the companies are also under scrutiny," said a source.

news.title: No occupier can acquire land title by adverse possession: Madras HC
news.para: The occupier can plead and prove title by adverse possession only as long as the government property remains as a government poramboke, not being reserved for any public purposes.

news.title: Sale of Lutyens bungalow under Delhi HC lens
news.para: Punit Beriwala, the Vipul MD, moved the high court after Bhai Manjit Singh’s lawyer issued a public notice of sale. Beriwala claimed that the property cannot be sold to anyone else since he had made an advance payment.

news.title: Mindspace REIT's net operating income up 4% to Rs 371.5 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Mindspace Business Parks REIT CEO Vinod Rohira said the company witnessed a significant uptick of leasing activity with around 1.8 million square feet of space leased in the December quarter, taking the overall leasing to around 3.8 million square feet the first nine months of FY22.
